OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Fri 19 Jun to Sun 28 Jun
OL,6,FThere is the possibility of some hot
OL,7,Fand humid weather across parts of
OL,8,Fsouth and southeast Britain at the
OL,9,Fstart of this period and with it comes
OL,10,Fthe chance of a few thunderstorms too.
OL,11,FTo the northwest of here, generally
OL,12,Fmore changeable at first, but there is
OL,13,Fa signal for high pressure to build
OL,14,Fmore widely as we move towards the
OL,15,Flatter part of June. This could bring
OL,16,Fmore widely drier, settled conditions
OL,17,Fwith temperatures probably remaining
OL,18,Fabove average for most. There is
OL,19,Fchance however that the hot
OL,20,Fconditions, initially in the south
OL,21,Fcould either linger here or, having
OL,22,Fwaned for a time, return northwards
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Faccompanied by a thunderstorm risk;
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fthis all dependent on the orientation
OL,25,Fof the aforementioned high pressure.
